Army Major John Jackson and his wife Carolyn are on trial for abusing their three foster children . 
  Their first child abuse trial was ruled a mistrial when a prosecutor mentioned the death of one of the children . 
  The Jacksons are accused of forcing the children to drink hot sauce and eat hot pepper flakes . 
  The children were left with broken bones and other health problems . 
  John and Carolyn Jackson had three biological children and three adopted children . 
 